var PI = 3.14;
PI = 42; // stop me from doing this!

const PI = 3.14;
PI = 3.14;
/* Write an ES2015 Version */


What is the difference between var and let?
- Let creates a block scope and cannot be redeclared but can be reassigned. Var can be reassigned and redeclared.

What is the difference between var and const?
-Const is a block scope and cannot be reassigned or redeclared. Var can be reassigned and redeclared. Var can also be hoisted variable.

What is the difference between let and const?
-Let can be reassigned but not redeclared while const cannot reassigned or be redeclared.

What is hoisting?
- Hoisting is the mechanism where all declarations like functions and variables are moved to the top of scored before the execution of the code.
